<DocsLayout
  title="Speech"
  eyebrow="Capabilities"
  description="Provider-neutral speech-to-text for clients that capture audio."
  prev={{ href: "/docs/media-generation/", title: "Media generation" }}
  next={{ href: "/docs/usage-analytics/", title: "Usage analytics" }}
>
  <p>
    Roder exposes a provider-neutral speech-to-text service. Clients own microphone
    capture and encoding; Roder accepts bounded audio payloads and normalizes provider
    results into text, language, duration, segments, and metadata.
  </p>

  <h2>Providers</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>openai-speech</code> supports OpenAI transcription models including <code>gpt-4o-mini-transcribe</code> and <code>whisper-1</code>.</li>
    <li><code>google-speech</code> supports Google Speech-to-Text with access tokens, API keys, or authorized-user ADC.</li>
  </ul>

  <pre><code>roder speech providers
roder speech transcribe clip.wav --provider openai-speech --model gpt-4o-mini-transcribe
cat clip.wav | roder speech transcribe - --format json
roder speech transcribe clip.wav --to-thread &lt;thread-id&gt;</code></pre>

  <p>
    Raw audio is not stored in thread transcripts. API transcript recording redacts audio
    bytes and sensitive headers before writing JSONL. Sending a transcript into a turn is
    explicit via <code>--to-thread</code>; audio never starts a turn silently.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
